    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a mechanically sound example of the E46 platform, powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine featuring individual throttle bodies and a factory-rated 8,000 RPM redline. To ensure longevity, the critical rod bearing service has been completed, and the dual-VANOS system has been overhauled for optimal variable valve timing performance. The 6-speed Getrag manual transmission shifts with precision, delivering power to the rear wheels via the M-Variable differential lock. Crucially, the rear subframe mounting points have been inspected and reinforced to address common chassis fatigue. The suspension retains its factory-tuned geometry, providing the communicative feedback expected of the M-division. While the finish shows minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver's car, the mechanical vitals\u2014including a refreshed cooling system and updated bushings\u2014make this a performance-ready icon for the discerning enthusiast.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
