      "description": "Offered is a mechanically robust 997.1 Carrera, powered by the 3.6L flat-six M97 engine utilizing VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve. This example features a 6-speed manual transaxle with crisp synchro engagement and a recently serviced dual-mass flywheel. The chassis dynamics are maintained by a Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) system, ensuring precise lateral stability and damping. The braking system utilizes four-piston aluminum monobloc fixed calipers over cross-drilled, vented rotors, showing minimal swept-area wear. This vehicle has been maintained with an emphasis on mechanical longevity, including a verified IMS inspection and a cooling system overhaul. A highly capable enthusiast spec ready for spirited driving.",
